Description: Sampling points of a data set (typically time or frequency).
Values of a data set with respect to a data grid. The data set has the value $f_i$ at data grid point $x_i$.
The number of the index of a data or data grid point.
Time between two successive data points, e.g. two images (for fixed temporal resolution).
The axial length of a cylindrical object, e.g. a capillary.
The spatial position within a cylindrical object, e.g. a capillary. In the case of a capillary x=0 denotes the arterial inlet position and x=L<sub>ax</sub> the venous outlet position.
A constant value which can be used e.g. for scaling.
The lower value at which the behavior of a function or algorithm changes.
The upper value at which the behavior of a function or algorithm changes.
A function of an independent variable *x* (typically time or frequency) with value $f(x_i)$ at data grid point $x_i$.
The start point of the range [$x_{start}$, $x_{end}$].
The end point of the range [$x_{start}$, $x_{end}$].
The number samples within a data set.

OSIPI name: Quantity not listed
Description: This is a custom free-text item, which can be used if a quantity of interest is not listed. Please state a literature reference and request the item to be added to the lexicon for future usage.
